!TITLE
HE KNOWS THE FEELING
!WORDS
The book "Black Like Me" told the story of John Griffin, a white man 
who darkened his skin in an effort to understand what it meant to be 
black in a predominantly white society.  More recently, a 30-year-old 
woman, an industrial designer, masqueraded as an elderly woman once a 
week for 3 years.  She was trying to see how it feels to be old in 
America.  What she learned is heart- breaking.  She was robbed, 
insulted, and frightened by a world that isn't easy on its elderly.
