!TITLE
A GOOD MOTHER'S INFLUENCE
!WORDS
We set aside one day a year to honor mothers.  The majority of them 
deserve it, and they truly are VIPs.  Abraham Lincoln declared, "no 
man is poor who has had a godly mother."  A Spanish proverb reads, 
"An ounce of mother is worth a ton of priest."  Someone else has 
said, "The instruction received at Mother's knee, together with the 
pious and sweet souvenirs of the fireside, are never effaced entirely 
from the soul."
