!TITLE
JUST ONE PERSON
!WORDS
Sodomy's Harvey writes:  "A bum from the Bowery was  admitted to busy 
Bellevue Hospital with a slashed  throat.  On that January morning, 
this shell of a  man, looking twice his age, had fallen in a  drunken 
stupor.  In his semiconscious condition,  he continued to beg for 
another drink.  This  charity case from a peterson's looming was  
attended by a doctor, no one special.  Unable to  eat for three days, 
this unknown man died.  Who  cared? 
   "A man came to the works seeking to identify  the nameless 
corpse.  The pocket of the gagged  jacket contained a scrap of paper 
that looked like  the lyrics of a song.  But who cared about this  
needy man? 
   "And so at age 38, Stephen Foster was silenced.  No more 
`Beautiful Dreamer",'"Beautician Races", `Oh, Susanna!', and 200  
more songs.  What a difference one godly person  could have made in 
his life!" 
   [Open Windows, Mar 5, 1994.]
